4. Clean up the .gitlab-ci.yml preserve handling in tasks/main.yml

Your current main.yml is close, but I would make it easier to read by setting a skip variable first.

Replace the .gitlab-ci.yml section in tasks/main.yml with this:

- name: "Check root .gitlab-ci.yml for preserve handling"
  ansible.builtin.stat:
    path: "{{ repo_environment_init_gitlab_ci_file }}"
  register: repo_environment_init_gitlab_ci_preserve_stat
  when:
    - repo_environment_init_manage_gitlab_ci | bool
    - repo_environment_init_respect_preserve_file | bool
- name: "Set root .gitlab-ci.yml skip state"
  ansible.builtin.set_fact:
    repo_environment_init_gitlab_ci_should_skip: >-
      {{
        repo_environment_init_manage_gitlab_ci | bool
        and repo_environment_init_respect_preserve_file | bool
        and not repo_environment_init_overwrite_existing | bool
        and repo_environment_init_gitlab_ci_preserve_stat.stat.exists | default(false)
        and '.gitlab-ci.yml' in (repo_environment_init_active_preserve_entries | default([]))
      }}
  when:
    - repo_environment_init_manage_gitlab_ci | bool
- name: "Skip preserved root .gitlab-ci.yml"
  ansible.builtin.debug:
    msg: "Preserving existing root .gitlab-ci.yml because it is listed in .sync-preserve."
  when:
    - repo_environment_init_gitlab_ci_should_skip | default(false) | bool
- name: Manage root .gitlab-ci.yml
  import_tasks: manage_gitlab_ci.yml
  when:
    - repo_environment_init_manage_gitlab_ci | bool
    - not (repo_environment_init_gitlab_ci_should_skip | default(false) | bool)

This means manage_gitlab_ci.yml does not need to be changed right now. The role will simply skip importing that file when .gitlab-ci.yml is preserved.

