On the second run, you want to see this pattern:

Skip preserved existing path ansible/inventory
ok: [localhost]
Back up existing managed path ansible/inventory
skipping: [localhost]
Copy managed directory ansible/inventory
skipping: [localhost]

For .gitlab-ci.yml, you want to see:

Skip preserved root .gitlab-ci.yml
ok: [localhost]
Manage root .gitlab-ci.yml
skipping: [localhost]

If you see Back up existing managed path ... changed again for a preserved path, then the issue is not the copy task anymore — it means .sync-preserve does not contain the matching entry or the active preserve list is not being loaded the way we expect.